Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It allows you to enjoy a book without getting a headache from reading.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It also allows you more time to hear the story especially when driving.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There are disadvantages to listening to an audiobook.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: No longer do you need to pay for an audiobook.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think that depends on what your situation is and why you are reading.
